{"_id":"SkuttDream","name":"Skutt the Moose - Dream Projection","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-blue-green.webp","system":{"npcType":"creature","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a majestic and magnificent moose","I protect the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all my might"],"agenda":"Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that this perfect world is just a wishful illusion","background":"This is not the real Skutt, but a dream projection created by Princess Tuvstarr. He appears healthy and majestic, always near the Princess, following her as she rides him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt has no recollection of the Hunters or the real world. However, a spark of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection - a part of his soul that knows this perfect world is just an illusion. This spark can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember the real world and what has happened because of Tuvstarr's wish. Unlike his corrupted spectral counterpart in the real world, this Skutt is whole, beautiful, and strong - everything the real Skutt once was before tragedy struck."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"dream-guardian","location":"dream-world","nature":"illusion-with-spark-of-truth"}}
{"_id":"SkuttMoose","name":"Skutt the Moose - Spectral Guardian","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/elk-moose-marked-green.webp","system":{"npcType":"creature","oppositionLevel":7,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a majestic and magnificent moose","Ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr's magic which keeps me alive"],"agenda":"I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can't get in / Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the world rot away","gifts":[{"name":"Spectral Presence","description":"Skutt cannot truly be eliminated as long as Tuvstarr's wish keeps him alive. The moose can move through fog, disappearing and reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one can stop or impede Skutt's movement. When he suffers his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the following Scene."}],"background":"Once the majestic King of the Woods, Skutt met Princess Tuvstarr and couldn't refuse when she asked to see the world. He took her to the black pond where wishes come true, but when she disappeared into the waters, a crack appeared in the sky and froze the sun forever. When a knight attacked him, Skutt killed the warrior but was mortally wounded by a spear. However, Tuvstarr's wish that he exist forever wouldn't let him die. Now he is rotting, crawling with worms that hatch into ghostly moths around his horns. A torn knightly cloak hangs from his antlers, and a spear remains half-driven into his body. He wanders in shame, surrounded by fog and the stench of death, desperately seeking someone who can save Tuvstarr without endangering her."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"tragic-guardian","status":"undead-spectral"}}
{"_id":"StalloTroll","name":"Stallo - The Old Troll","type":"npc","img":"icons/creatures/unholy/giant-troll-forest-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"creature","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am an old troll and my appetite is matched only by my strength","A bird has made its nest on my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the eye, which is incredibly annoying!"],"gifts":[{"name":"Troll","description":"Stallo possesses enormous strength and each Position Check for a physical action attempted against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, only to regenerate within minutes."}],"background":"An old troll sleeping under a tree in the cursed forest. A bird has built a nest in his hair, and when disturbed it pecks at his eye, causing him great annoyance. If awakened by too much noise or for any other reason, Stallo will try to eat the intruders. His enormous strength and regenerative abilities make him a formidable opponent, though he can be avoided if travelers are careful and quiet."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"forest-hazard","behavior":"sleeps-until-disturbed"}}
{"_id":"SwampFairies","name":"The Fairies","type":"npc","img":"icons/magic/light/orbs-smoke-blue.webp","system":{"npcType":"creature","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["We are Fairies, spirits of nature","We move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans"],"agenda":"Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and dance forever wrapped in its sweet light","gifts":[{"name":"Madness","description":"Made mad by the light of the crown, the Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a Defense Check against OL Medium 5."}],"background":"Ethereal spirits of nature who look like pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in the air as if adrift in an invisible current. Their eyes are shut and they moan with pleasure as they bask in the light from Tuvstarr's golden crown. Corrupted by the crown's splendor, they guard it obsessively in the swamps, surrounded by the bodies of all those who have drowned there over the centuries - corpses that have emerged from the earth to watch the Fairies dance. The Fairies are dreamlike and ethereal, their bodies passing through each other. Around the crown there are always twelve fairies. If someone blocks the light from the crown, they will awaken screaming in agony at seeing how corrupted the lands have become."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"tuvstarrs-reflection","role":"crown-guardians","location":"swamp","usage":"use-multiple-twelve"}}
